---
title: Chermoula Crusted Coley with Roasted Carrot Freekah Salad
description: Coley is a great tasting white fish with a similar meaty texture to Cod making it a versatile ingredient to use for a light and fresh midweek dinner. It’s flaky texture works brilliantly with the crunchy chermoula crumb which can be prepped in minutes for show stopping results. Served with nutty freekeh salad (it should retain its bite when cooked) and a zesty yoghurt dressing, this is a quick and tasty recipe you can go wrong with.
